<p><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-FeanorStar7-2007-04-27T07:24:00.000Z-Include_usurpers_on_list?"></span>I see that <a href="/wiki/Mezezius" class="mw-redirect" title="Mezezius">Mezezius</a> (a usurper) is included, but several 5th century usurpers (e.g. <a href="/wiki/Constans_II_(usurper)" class="mw-redirect" title="Constans II (usurper)">Constans II (usurper)</a>) are not included in the template. What is the criterion for inclusion on the template?--<a href="/wiki/User:FeanorStar7" title="User:FeanorStar7">FeanorStar7</a> 07:24, 27 April 2007 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-FeanorStar7-2007-04-27T07:24:00.000Z-Include_usurpers_on_list?"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2007-04-27T07:24:00.000Z","author":"FeanorStar7","type":"comment","level":1,"id":"c-FeanorStar7-2007-04-27T07:24:00.000Z-Include_usurpers_on_list?","replies":["c-TAnthony-2007-04-27T08:42:00.000Z-FeanorStar7-2007-04-27T07:24:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-FeanorStar7-2007-04-27T07:24:00.000Z-Include_usurpers_on_list?"></span>
</p>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-TAnthony-2007-04-27T08:42:00.000Z-FeanorStar7-2007-04-27T07:24:00.000Z"></span>I cleaned up/revised this template from a previously messy version without knowing much about many of the later "emperors"; I think any usurpers should be added, especially if they have coins, LOL. Seriously, the template is meant as a navigation tool, and usurpers have a place there too. <a href="/wiki/User:TAnthony" title="User:TAnthony">TAnthony</a> 08:42, 27 April 2007 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-TAnthony-2007-04-27T08:42:00.000Z-FeanorStar7-2007-04-27T07:24:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2007-04-27T08:42:00.000Z","author":"TAnthony","type":"comment","level":2,"id":"c-TAnthony-2007-04-27T08:42:00.000Z-FeanorStar7-2007-04-27T07:24:00.000Z","replies":["c-Pmanderson-2008-07-15T17:10:00.000Z-TAnthony-2007-04-27T08:42:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-TAnthony-2007-04-27T08:42:00.000Z-FeanorStar7-2007-04-27T07:24:00.000Z"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Pmanderson-2008-07-15T17:10:00.000Z-TAnthony-2007-04-27T08:42:00.000Z"></span>No; consider the  number of usurpers, most of whom have coins. This template is already enormous without the <a href="/wiki/Thirty_Tyrants_(Roman)" title="Thirty Tyrants (Roman)">Thirty Tyrants (Roman)</a> and the Emperors of Britain. <a href="/wiki/User:Pmanderson" title="User:Pmanderson">Septentrionalis</a> <small><a href="/wiki/User_talk:Pmanderson" title="User talk:Pmanderson">PMAnderson</a></small> 17:10, 15 July 2008 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Pmanderson-2008-07-15T17:10:00.000Z-TAnthony-2007-04-27T08:42:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2008-07-15T17:10:00.000Z","author":"Pmanderson","type":"comment","level":3,"id":"c-Pmanderson-2008-07-15T17:10:00.000Z-TAnthony-2007-04-27T08:42:00.000Z","replies":[],"displayName":"Septentrionalis"}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Pmanderson-2008-07-15T17:10:00.000Z-TAnthony-2007-04-27T08:42:00.000Z"></span></dd></dl></dd></dl>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2 ext-discussiontools-init-section"><!--__DTSUBSCRIBEBUTTONDESKTOP__{&quot;headingLevel&quot;:2,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;h-Rst20xx-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:0,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;h-Revert_to_recent_edit-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;replies&quot;:[&quot;c-Rst20xx-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z-Revert_to_recent_edit&quot;],&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Revert to recent edit&quot;,&quot;linkableTitle&quot;:&quot;Revert to recent edit&quot;}--><h2 data-mw-thread-id="h-Revert_to_recent_edit-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z"><span class="mw-headline" id="Revert_to_recent_edit"><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-Revert_to_recent_edit-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z"></span>Revert to recent edit<span data-mw-comment-end="h-Revert_to_recent_edit-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Template_talk:Roman_emperors&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Revert to recent edit"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"headingLevel":2,"name":"h-Rst20xx-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z","type":"heading","level":0,"id":"h-Revert_to_recent_edit-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z","replies":["c-Rst20xx-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z-Revert_to_recent_edit"]}}--><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-bar"><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-metadata"><!--__DTLATESTCOMMENTTHREAD__{"id":"c-Rst20xx-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z-Revert_to_recent_edit","timestamp":"2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z"}__--><!--__DTCOMMENTCOUNT__1__--><!--__DTAUTHORCOUNT__1__--></div><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-actions"><!--__DTSUBSCRIBEBUTTONMOBILE__{&quot;headingLevel&quot;:2,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;h-Rst20xx-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:0,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;h-Revert_to_recent_edit-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;replies&quot;:[&quot;c-Rst20xx-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z-Revert_to_recent_edit&quot;],&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Revert to recent edit&quot;,&quot;linkableTitle&quot;:&quot;Revert to recent edit&quot;}--></div></div></div>
<p><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Rst20xx-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z-Revert_to_recent_edit"></span>I reverted <a href="/wiki/User:The_President_of_Cool" title="User:The President of Cool">The President of Cool</a>'s 26 April edit, which he made citing that "during most of this time no one person ruled the entire empire". But the problems here are:
1. Dates aren't always precise when it comes to the Roman Emperors, so at least something in his edit will probably be wrong
2. There are overlapping reigns throughout all periods of the Empire, so by his logic all sections should be changed like this. This template has rulers sorted by the date they first became Emperor, which works!
3. Look what it does to the size of the template!
- <a href="/wiki/User:Rst20xx" title="User:Rst20xx">rst20xx</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Rst20xx" title="User talk:Rst20xx">talk</a>) 00:24, 27 April 2008 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Rst20xx-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z-Revert_to_recent_edit"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z","author":"Rst20xx","type":"comment","level":1,"id":"c-Rst20xx-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z-Revert_to_recent_edit","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Rst20xx-2008-04-27T00:24:00.000Z-Revert_to_recent_edit"></span>
