<p><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-*Treker-2018-11-20T17:47:00.000Z-Usurpers:_bold_vs_underlining"></span>Could we maybe use bold for them instead of underlining? It's a little confusing when hovering over the names when they're already underlined.<a href="/wiki/User:*Treker" class="mw-redirect" title="User:*Treker">★Trekker</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:*Treker" class="mw-redirect" title="User talk:*Treker">talk</a>) 17:47, 20 November 2018 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-*Treker-2018-11-20T17:47:00.000Z-Usurpers:_bold_vs_underlining"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2018-11-20T17:47:00.000Z","author":"*Treker","type":"comment","level":1,"id":"c-*Treker-2018-11-20T17:47:00.000Z-Usurpers:_bold_vs_underlining","replies":["c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T18:42:00.000Z-*Treker-2018-11-20T17:47:00.000Z"],"displayName":"\u2605Trekker"}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-*Treker-2018-11-20T17:47:00.000Z-Usurpers:_bold_vs_underlining"></span>
</p>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T18:42:00.000Z-*Treker-2018-11-20T17:47:00.000Z"></span>With the question raised, should they be included at all? Do infoboxes of other "monarchies" include usurpers as well? In either case, bolding might be more appropriate for actual ruling emperors if differentiation is to be applied as it definitely makes something stand out more. <a href="/wiki/User:Ichthyovenator" title="User:Ichthyovenator">Ichthyovenator</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Ichthyovenator" title="User talk:Ichthyovenator">talk</a>) 18:42, 20 November 2018 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T18:42:00.000Z-*Treker-2018-11-20T17:47:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2018-11-20T18:42:00.000Z","author":"Ichthyovenator","type":"comment","level":2,"id":"c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T18:42:00.000Z-*Treker-2018-11-20T17:47:00.000Z","replies":["c-Dimadick-2018-11-20T19:15:00.000Z-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T18:42:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T18:42:00.000Z-*Treker-2018-11-20T17:47:00.000Z"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Dimadick-2018-11-20T19:15:00.000Z-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T18:42:00.000Z"></span>But most of the "usurpers" were reigning emperors, holding large territories. Usurpation was just the method by which they ceased the throne. <a href="/wiki/User:Dimadick" title="User:Dimadick">Dimadick</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Dimadick" title="User talk:Dimadick">talk</a>) 19:15, 20 November 2018 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Dimadick-2018-11-20T19:15:00.000Z-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T18:42:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2018-11-20T19:15:00.000Z","author":"Dimadick","type":"comment","level":3,"id":"c-Dimadick-2018-11-20T19:15:00.000Z-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T18:42:00.000Z","replies":["c-*Treker-2018-11-20T19:42:00.000Z-Dimadick-2018-11-20T19:15:00.000Z","c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T19:50:00.000Z-Dimadick-2018-11-20T19:15:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Dimadick-2018-11-20T19:15:00.000Z-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T18:42:00.000Z"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-*Treker-2018-11-20T19:42:00.000Z-Dimadick-2018-11-20T19:15:00.000Z"></span>Either way I don't care for the underlining.<a href="/wiki/User:*Treker" class="mw-redirect" title="User:*Treker">★Trekker</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:*Treker" class="mw-redirect" title="User talk:*Treker">talk</a>) 19:42, 20 November 2018 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-*Treker-2018-11-20T19:42:00.000Z-Dimadick-2018-11-20T19:15:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2018-11-20T19:42:00.000Z","author":"*Treker","type":"comment","level":4,"id":"c-*Treker-2018-11-20T19:42:00.000Z-Dimadick-2018-11-20T19:15:00.000Z","replies":[],"displayName":"\u2605Trekker"}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-*Treker-2018-11-20T19:42:00.000Z-Dimadick-2018-11-20T19:15:00.000Z"></span></dd>
<dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T19:50:00.000Z-Dimadick-2018-11-20T19:15:00.000Z"></span>This is of course true, but the same can surely be said of some other examples of historical usurpers? Something to note is that the usurpers are left out of the <a href="/wiki/List_of_Roman_emperors" title="List of Roman emperors">List of Roman emperors</a>. Another thing that complicates it a bit, I suppose, is that legitimacy is difficult to determine without a legal line of succession, especially for something as muddled as the Crisis of the Third Century. There are also examples where emperors seen by contemporaries as usurpers, e.g. <a href="/wiki/Romulus_Augustulus" title="Romulus Augustulus">Romulus Augustulus</a>, have been regarded as full emperors in later historiography. In either case, I don't think making the usurpers bold in this template is a good solution though I agree that underlining isn't very good either. In the <a href="/wiki/Template:English,_Scottish_and_British_monarchs" title="Template:English, Scottish and British monarchs">british monarchs template</a>, disputed monarchs are in italics which I think looks quite good but that is already used for co-emperors here. <a href="/wiki/User:Ichthyovenator" title="User:Ichthyovenator">Ichthyovenator</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Ichthyovenator" title="User talk:Ichthyovenator">talk</a>) 19:50, 20 November 2018 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T19:50:00.000Z-Dimadick-2018-11-20T19:15:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2018-11-20T19:50:00.000Z","author":"Ichthyovenator","type":"comment","level":4,"id":"c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T19:50:00.000Z-Dimadick-2018-11-20T19:15:00.000Z","replies":["c-*Treker-2018-11-20T20:03:00.000Z-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T19:50:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T19:50:00.000Z-Dimadick-2018-11-20T19:15:00.000Z"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-*Treker-2018-11-20T20:03:00.000Z-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T19:50:00.000Z"></span>Maybe we can bold common emperors and leave the usurpers regular?<a href="/wiki/User:*Treker" class="mw-redirect" title="User:*Treker">★Trekker</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:*Treker" class="mw-redirect" title="User talk:*Treker">talk</a>) 20:03, 20 November 2018 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-*Treker-2018-11-20T20:03:00.000Z-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T19:50:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2018-11-20T20:03:00.000Z","author":"*Treker","type":"comment","level":5,"id":"c-*Treker-2018-11-20T20:03:00.000Z-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T19:50:00.000Z","replies":["c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T20:42:00.000Z-*Treker-2018-11-20T20:03:00.000Z"],"displayName":"\u2605Trekker"}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-*Treker-2018-11-20T20:03:00.000Z-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T19:50:00.000Z"></span>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T20:42:00.000Z-*Treker-2018-11-20T20:03:00.000Z"></span>That would of course mean bolding a vast majority of the names. <a href="/wiki/User:Ichthyovenator" title="User:Ichthyovenator">Ichthyovenator</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Ichthyovenator" title="User talk:Ichthyovenator">talk</a>) 20:42, 20 November 2018 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T20:42:00.000Z-*Treker-2018-11-20T20:03:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2018-11-20T20:42:00.000Z","author":"Ichthyovenator","type":"comment","level":6,"id":"c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T20:42:00.000Z-*Treker-2018-11-20T20:03:00.000Z","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T20:42:00.000Z-*Treker-2018-11-20T20:03:00.000Z"></span></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl>
<p><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Dimadick-2018-11-20T20:14:00.000Z-Usurpers:_bold_vs_underlining"></span>"are left out of the List of Roman emperors."
</p><p>Because we already have <a href="/wiki/List_of_Roman_usurpers" title="List of Roman usurpers">List of Roman usurpers</a> and a <a href="/wiki/List_of_Byzantine_usurpers" title="List of Byzantine usurpers">List of Byzantine usurpers</a>. Covering people from the 1st to the 15th century. <a href="/wiki/User:Dimadick" title="User:Dimadick">Dimadick</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Dimadick" title="User talk:Dimadick">talk</a>) 20:14, 20 November 2018 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Dimadick-2018-11-20T20:14:00.000Z-Usurpers:_bold_vs_underlining"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2018-11-20T20:14:00.000Z","author":"Dimadick","type":"comment","level":1,"id":"c-Dimadick-2018-11-20T20:14:00.000Z-Usurpers:_bold_vs_underlining","replies":["c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T20:41:00.000Z-Dimadick-2018-11-20T20:14:00.000Z"]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Dimadick-2018-11-20T20:14:00.000Z-Usurpers:_bold_vs_underlining"></span>
</p>
<dl><dd><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T20:41:00.000Z-Dimadick-2018-11-20T20:14:00.000Z"></span>I'm aware, just pointing it out. There is also a point to be made that there are several Roman usurpers left out of going by the <a href="/wiki/List_of_Roman_usurpers" title="List of Roman usurpers">List of Roman usurpers</a> and that Byzantine usurpers are left out entirely. <a href="/wiki/User:Ichthyovenator" title="User:Ichthyovenator">Ichthyovenator</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Ichthyovenator" title="User talk:Ichthyovenator">talk</a>) 20:41, 20 November 2018 (UTC)<span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-buttons" data-mw-thread-id="c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T20:41:00.000Z-Dimadick-2018-11-20T20:14:00.000Z"><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">[</span><a class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-reply" role="button" tabindex="0" href="">reply</a><span class="ext-discussiontools-init-replylink-bracket">]</span><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"timestamp":"2018-11-20T20:41:00.000Z","author":"Ichthyovenator","type":"comment","level":2,"id":"c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T20:41:00.000Z-Dimadick-2018-11-20T20:14:00.000Z","replies":[]}}--></span><span data-mw-comment-end="c-Ichthyovenator-2018-11-20T20:41:00.000Z-Dimadick-2018-11-20T20:14:00.000Z"></span></dd></dl>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2 ext-discussiontools-init-section"><!--__DTSUBSCRIBEBUTTONDESKTOP__{&quot;headingLevel&quot;:2,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;h-*Treker-2021-11-12T12:52:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:0,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;h-Ulpia_and_Eudokia-2021-11-12T12:52:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;replies&quot;:[&quot;c-*Treker-2021-11-12T12:52:00.000Z-Ulpia_and_Eudokia&quot;],&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Ulpia and Eudokia&quot;,&quot;linkableTitle&quot;:&quot;Ulpia and Eudokia&quot;}--><h2 data-mw-thread-id="h-Ulpia_and_Eudokia-2021-11-12T12:52:00.000Z"><span class="mw-headline" id="Ulpia_and_Eudokia"><span data-mw-comment-start="" id="h-Ulpia_and_Eudokia-2021-11-12T12:52:00.000Z"></span>Ulpia and Eudokia<span data-mw-comment-end="h-Ulpia_and_Eudokia-2021-11-12T12:52:00.000Z"></span></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Template_talk:Roman_emperors&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Ulpia and Eudokia"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2><!--__DTELLIPSISBUTTON__{"threadItem":{"headingLevel":2,"name":"h-*Treker-2021-11-12T12:52:00.000Z","type":"heading","level":0,"id":"h-Ulpia_and_Eudokia-2021-11-12T12:52:00.000Z","replies":["c-*Treker-2021-11-12T12:52:00.000Z-Ulpia_and_Eudokia"]}}--><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-bar"><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-metadata"><!--__DTLATESTCOMMENTTHREAD__{"id":"c-Ichthyovenator-2021-11-12T14:47:00.000Z-Ichthyovenator-2021-11-12T14:18:00.000Z","timestamp":"2021-11-12T14:47:00.000Z"}__--><!--__DTCOMMENTCOUNT__3__--><!--__DTAUTHORCOUNT__2__--></div><div class="ext-discussiontools-init-section-actions"><!--__DTSUBSCRIBEBUTTONMOBILE__{&quot;headingLevel&quot;:2,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;h-*Treker-2021-11-12T12:52:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:0,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;h-Ulpia_and_Eudokia-2021-11-12T12:52:00.000Z&quot;,&quot;rep